laboratory_examinations.findings: Hematocrit of 22.7 percent on postoperative day 0, increased to 30.6 percent after treatment with 4 units of packed red blood cells.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Hematocrit increased from 22.7 percent to 30.6 percent.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Systolic blood pressures between 80 and 95 mmHg initially, elevated to 120 to 130 mmHg after treatment with blood cells.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Systolic blood pressure increased from 80-95 mmHg to 120-130 mmHg.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Initially low urine output, improved after treatment with packed red blood cells.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Urine output increased after blood transfusion.
